      "cookedHtml": "<p>Hello,<br />\nHow can I user duration?<br />\nI found this article</p><aside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n      <img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/2X/9/98c06310a554814ff77088324e4c387821d30757.png\" class=\"site-icon\" width=\"152\" height=\"152\" />\n\n      <a href=\"https://support.monday.com/hc/en-us/articles/4417788326418-The-Timeline-Numeric-Combo-Column-The-Duration-Column\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Support</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <div class=\"aspect-image\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/optimized/1X/41f46e5e9ea124f10772b48bfbf05a8c96547b79_2_690x127.jpeg\" class=\"thumbnail\" width=\"690\" height=\"127\" /></div>\n\n<h3><a href=\"https://support.monday.com/hc/en-us/articles/4417788326418-The-Timeline-Numeric-Combo-Column-The-Duration-Column\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">The Timeline + Numeric Combo Column (The Duration Column)</a></h3>\n\n  <p>5 min read\n\n\nFeature\n\n\n \nLooking to instantly display the number of days that you've set in the Timeline Column? Or, conversely, are you wanting to automatically set a range of dates in your Timeli...</p>\n\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div></div>\n</aside>\n\n<p>But It looks like the Timeline + Numeric Combo view is now gone?</p>\n<p>thanks</p>"
